# Data Lineage Tracking

## Lineage Requirements

Every data transformation MUST record:
- Source entities (inputs)
- Transformation logic
- Destination entity (output)
- Timestamp
- Actor (who performed)
- Context (why performed)

## Lineage Tool

```
Tool: mldlc-lineage/record_lineage
Parameters:
  source_entities: ["entity_id_1", "entity_id_2"]
  transformation: "Description of transformation"
  destination_entity: "output_entity_id"
  context: "Why this transformation was performed"
  code_reference: "Link to code (optional)"
```

## Lineage Query

```
Tool: mldlc-lineage/get_lineage
Parameters:
  entity_id: "entity to trace"
  direction: "upstream" | "downstream" | "both"
  depth: 5
```

## Lineage Resources

- `lineage://entity/{id}` - Entity lineage
- `lineage://graph` - Full lineage graph
- `lineage://impact/{id}` - Impact analysis

## Lineage Prompts

- `/lineage-trace` - Trace lineage of entity
- `/lineage-impact` - Analyze impact of change
